  "texts": [
    "To obtain a better understanding on how the average active Ukrainian Twitter user changes over time, we visualize the average number of published tweets by a user in each language in Fig. 3a.",
    "From the figure, we can clearly see that there are substantial shifts.",
    "Overall, the average number of RU tweets per user decreases constantly over time (from over 6.5 to 2.1), the outbreak of the war being no exception.",
    "The average number of EN tweets decreases slightly until the war, where we notice a sudden uptick (from 0.7 to 2.8), followed by a steady decline.",
    "Meanwhile, the number of UA tweets slowly but steadily rises (from 2.4 to 2.9), with steeper increases after the first signs of aggression in November 2021 and no appearance of slowing down (5.3 at the end)."
  ],
